OL,3,CCourt told how sex crime victims could
OL,4,Cbe jailed under new law
OL,6,FVictims of sex crimes in Northern
OL,7,FIreland could face six months in
OL,8,Fprison if they publicly name their
OL,9,Fsuspected abusers under a new
OL,10,Fanonymity law, the High Court has
OL,11,Fheard.JAlleged perpetrators will also
OL,12,Funfairly remain protected from
OL,13,Fidentification for up to 25 years
OL,14,Fafter their death by the legislation
OL,15,Fwhich stymies public interest
OL,16,Fjournalism, it was claimed.JMedia
OL,17,Forganisations have joined forces in an
OL,18,Fattempt to have sections of the
OL,19,FJustice (Sexual Offences and
OL,20,FTrafficking Victims) Act (Northern
OL,21,FIreland) 2022 declared legally invalid.
