OL,3,CCourt told how sex crime victims could
OL,4,Cbe jailed under new law
OL,6,FCounsel for the Belfast Telegraph and
OL,7,FThe Irish News contended it was beyond
OL,8,FStormont's legislative competence to
OL,9,Fintroduce a law said to be
OL,10,Fincompatible with the European
OL,11,FConvention on Human Rights (ECHR).
OL,12,FDavid Dunlop KC submitted:
OL,13,F"Publishers, bloggers and individuals
OL,14,Fcan face up to six months imprisonment
OL,15,Fas a fairly draconian consequence of
OL,16,Fexpressing one's freedom of
OL,17,Fexpression."JThe Act prohibits
OL,18,Fdisclosing the identity of anyone
OL,19,Fsuspected of sex offences prior to
OL,20,Fbeing charged or until they have been
OL,21,Fdead for 25 years.JPassed by MLAs
OL,22,Ffollowing a review carried out by
OL,23,Fretired judge Sir John Gillen, it sets
OL,24,FNorthern Ireland apart from the rest
OL,25,Fof the United Kingdom and the Republic
OL,26,Fof Ireland.JConcerns have been
